BEGIN_HYPERDESC
<h1>HST servicing mission 1 (STS-61)</h1>
<p>After discovering major problems with Hubble's primary mirror, mission STS-61
is scheduled to capture the telescope and install the COSTAR corrective optics
package and the Wide Field and Planetary Camera 2 (WFPC2).</p>
<p>In this scenario, the Shuttle orbiter has already been maneuvered close to
Hubble's position. Move Atlantis into position using linear RCS thrusters, and
grapple with the manipulator arm. Use the Manned Maneuvering Unit (MMU) for an
EVA to perform the instrument replacements. (Keyboard: E)</p>
<p>In a departure from the historic mission, you can also try to return Hubble to
Earth. Switch focus to the HST to retract solar arrays, antennae and telescope hatch,
then stow the telescope in the Shuttle cargo bay. Return your valuable payload back
to KSC.</p>
END_HYPERDESC

